{
  "texts": [
    "RQ6: Vocabulary adaptation does not help much in case of extractive summaries, low OOV concentration and low novelty.",
    "We note that all the vocabulary adaptation techniques struggle to outperform both BASE and CPT-Only in Pub-MedQA (Llama-3.1), BioASQ-S (Llama-2), and BioASQ-M (Llama-2 and Llama-3.1).",
    "When compared in the entire test set; there is a performance drop of 1.39% across these two settings.",
    "This may be because PubMedQa and BioASQ-S have low novelty.",
    "Specifically, for BioASQ-S, the unigram novelty is just 4.11% (see Table 5), therefore, the high novelty threshold for top-ten percentile was 35%."
  ]
}